Annotation

Response Rate

Description

The percentage of sample members who provided information. This may include a broader description of stratified response rates, information affecting resonse rates etc.

Example

<respRate>For 1993, the estimated inclusion rate for TEDS-eligible providers was 91 percent, with the inclusion rate for all treatment providers estimated at 76 percent (including privately and publicly funded providers).</respRate> <respRate>The overall response rate was 82%, although retail firms with an annual sales volume of more than $5,000,000 were somewhat less likely to respond.</respRate>
